          "id": "cue-10c33bec58e2",
          "atMs": 250,
          "text": "A Java archive still needs a compatible JVM. A native binary built against a new glibc may refuse to start on an older distribution. Then x64, arm64, musl, graphics, media, browser, printing, storage, and desktop services all enter the delivery problem.",
          "caption": "A Java archive still needs a compatible JVM. A native binary built against a new glibc may refuse to start on an older distribution. Then x64, arm64, musl, graphics, media, browser, printing, storage, and desktop services all enter the delivery problem."
